00:53.387 --> 00:57.725
<i>I was born</i>
<i>in 1962 at Coral Gables Hospital,</i>

00:57.808 --> 01:01.812
<i>located on the University</i>
<i>of Miami campus.</i>

01:01.896 --> 01:04.940
<i>My parents like to brag</i>
<i>that their baby was so smart</i>

01:05.024 --> 01:08.736
<i>that she was already in college</i>
<i>the day she was born.</i>

01:08.819 --> 01:12.907
<i>I was given the name Cozy after</i>
<i>my father's favorite Jazz drummer-</i>

01:12.990 --> 01:14.909
<i>Cozy Cole.</i>

01:14.992 --> 01:17.453
<i>My mother left us when I was 10.</i>

01:17.536 --> 01:22.124
<i>My father always liked to say</i>
<i>that she ran away to join the circus.</i>

01:22.208 --> 01:26.504
<i>I like to think of her there in</i>
<i>a sequined cape flying through the air</i>

01:26.587 --> 01:29.590
<i>without a single net to catch her fall.</i>

01:29.673 --> 01:32.093
<i>Dad was never a religious man,</i>

01:32.176 --> 01:36.426
<i>but after Mom left,</i>
<i>he decided to raise me Catholic.</i>

01:36.555 --> 01:38.182
<i>On Sundays, I went to mass,</i>

01:38.265 --> 01:42.978
<i>and on the first Wednesday of every
month, I was sent to confession.</i>

01:43.062 --> 01:47.108
<i>Since I could never bring myself</i>
<i>to confess any of my real sins,</i>

01:47.191 --> 01:51.858
<i>I kept four made-up sins</i>
<i>that I used over and over again.</i>

01:52.822 --> 01:54.824
<i>Though Bobby and I</i>
<i>had never touched,</i>

01:54.907 --> 01:57.827
<i>he wrote me poems</i>
<i>all through high school.</i>

01:57.910 --> 02:01.664
<i>Later, I accepted his proposal</i>
<i>for marriage.</i>

02:01.747 --> 02:07.997
<i>I knew Bobby loved me and figured someday
I'd probably grow to love him too.</i>

02:08.795 --> 02:12.258
<i>We purchased our new home</i>
<i>through a city auction.</i>

02:12.341 --> 02:16.971
<i>The previous owner had murdered her husband
and buried him inside the shower wall.</i>

02:17.054 --> 02:20.182
<i>Bobby said</i>
<i>aside from being affordable,</i>

02:20.266 --> 02:23.933
<i>the house was also</i>
<i>a good conversation piece.</i>

02:26.939 --> 02:32.277
<i>I often thought about this woman and
wondered what made her act so violently.</i>

02:32.361 --> 02:34.196
<i>I guess it wasn't any one big thing,</i>

02:34.280 --> 02:40.447
<i>but a lot of little things that just grew</i>
<i>deeper and deeper under her skin.</i>

04:07.706 --> 04:09.500
Freeze! Police!

04:43.075 --> 04:47.997
<i>Most tourists visit the Miami area
for its beaches on the east coast,</i>

04:48.080 --> 04:53.377
<i>but if you ever mistakenly got on the
Palmetto Expressway and headed west,</i>

04:53.460 --> 04:56.880
<i>you'd run right into</i>
<i>the Florida Everglades,</i>

04:56.964 --> 05:01.343
<i>an area that Indians</i>
<i>like to call "the River of Grass."</i>

05:01.427 --> 05:04.638
<i>People used to think this area</i>
<i>was uninhabitable</i>

05:04.722 --> 05:07.474
<i>but more and more</i>
<i>it's becoming civilized,</i>

05:07.558 --> 05:09.518
<i>and they say that within two years</i>

05:09.601 --> 05:13.435
<i>there will be a shopping center</i>
<i>every 15 miles.</i>

05:27.411 --> 05:28.954
Thanks.

05:57.608 --> 06:01.862
<i>I've heard it said that the mother-child</i>
<i>bond begins at birth.</i>

06:01.945 --> 06:03.530
<i>For me, this Never occurred.</i>

06:03.614 --> 06:07.368
<i>And on some days,</i>
<i>I'd sit at my window for hours</i>

06:07.451 --> 06:13.873
<i>just waiting for a nice couple in a big station
wagon to come and take these kids away.</i>

06:13.957 --> 06:16.460
<i>Too much daydreaming left me blue.</i>

06:16.543 --> 06:19.421
<i>So while Bobby worked day and night,</i>

06:19.505 --> 06:23.755
<i>I stayed home and tried</i>
<i>to make the best of my time.</i>

06:47.658 --> 06:50.494
This guy's sitting at the bar
like a dead fish not talking to anyone,

06:50.577 --> 06:53.414
when this redhead comes up
and takes a seat next to him.

06:53.497 --> 06:55.416
They strike up a conversation.

06:55.499 --> 06:58.419
Eventually,
the conversation turns to sex.

06:58.502 --> 07:02.089
She says, "Great. I like kinky sex too.
Let's go to my place."

07:02.172 --> 07:04.172
So they go to her place.

07:05.008 --> 07:06.677
He goes in the bathroom.

07:06.760 --> 07:09.471
She takes off all of her clothes
and gets under the covers.

07:09.555 --> 07:13.559
After a couple of minutes, he comes out of
the bathroom. He's straightening his tie.

07:13.642 --> 07:15.519
He says- She says,
"Hey, where you going?"

07:15.602 --> 07:19.936
He says, "I'm through.
I already shit in your purse."

07:20.899 --> 07:23.026
Freeze! Police!

07:54.975 --> 07:56.810
Well, that's the best one I know.

07:56.894 --> 08:00.978
If that doesn't help,
I can only offer more booze.

08:04.485 --> 08:08.530
<i>It's funny how</i>
<i>a single day could drag and drag</i>

08:08.614 --> 08:12.114
<i>while entire years</i>
<i>just flip by in a flash.</i>

08:13.494 --> 08:17.164
<i>Once I calculated</i>
<i>how many hours old I was</i>

08:17.247 --> 08:21.501
<i>and then estimated how many</i>
<i>more hours there were to go.</i>

08:21.585 --> 08:23.086
<i>On another day,</i>

08:23.170 --> 08:26.757
<i>I made a list of every person</i>
<i>I had ever known.</i>

08:26.840 --> 08:29.218
<i>I wondered if any of these people</i>
<i>knew each other</i>

08:29.301 --> 08:32.888
<i>and if there was any chance</i>
<i>that they were all together now</i>

08:32.971 --> 08:36.308
<i>having a party or swimming in a pool.</i>

08:36.390 --> 08:42.313
<i>Then I wondered if there was any other
person on this planet as lonely as me.</i>

08:42.397 --> 08:47.814
<i>As it turned out, there was,</i>
<i>and he was living just a county away.</i>

09:26.817 --> 09:28.860
8:00, Lee.

10:45.729 --> 10:49.358
First thing this morning, right,
my dad's out on a run.

10:49.441 --> 10:53.153
So I'm just, like,
hanging out, having a cigarette,

10:53.236 --> 10:56.323
and I notice something on the end
of the road there, you know.

10:56.406 --> 10:58.533
I couldn't really make out what it was.

10:58.617 --> 11:01.662
From here, it looked like a gun.

11:01.745 --> 11:04.873
So we go over to check it out.

11:04.956 --> 11:09.920
Sure enough there it is- a fucking gun
laying right at the edge of the street.

11:10.003 --> 11:13.840
What, like a real gun?
Yes, like a very real gun.

11:13.924 --> 11:17.844
I got it hidden in the back there
in some boxes. It makes me nervous.

11:17.928 --> 11:19.513
Well, what kind of gun?

11:19.596 --> 11:22.641
I don't know.
It's black with a brown handle.

11:22.724 --> 11:24.726
Do you know anything about guns?

11:24.810 --> 11:27.229
Doug,
you coming to work today?

11:27.312 --> 11:30.148
Look, you gonna be around later?
I'll bring it on by.

11:30.232 --> 11:32.025
Julie giving you the night out?

11:32.109 --> 11:34.695
Working a little late.
You gonna be around or-

11:34.778 --> 11:36.154
Yeah, I'm around.

11:36.238 --> 11:39.488
Shoot up the neighborhood.
Sure, Dougie.

11:56.133 --> 11:58.552
You sick or something?

11:58.635 --> 12:00.429
Hi, Dad.

12:00.512 --> 12:03.557
Oh, you smell like a bottle of gin.

12:03.640 --> 12:05.308
I'm doing a little undercover work,

12:05.392 --> 12:10.647
