35:28.377 --> 35:30.504
Well, give me something to smash it with.
Well, hold on.

35:30.587 --> 35:34.007
Shit! We don't even
have our shoes.

35:35.592 --> 35:37.219
Here!

35:38.762 --> 35:40.973
Ahh!
Did you get him?

35:41.056 --> 35:43.851
Give me another Bible.
Here! Here!

35:43.934 --> 35:44.852
Shoot it!

35:47.896 --> 35:50.816
I think I peed in my pants.

35:50.899 --> 35:52.359
Is it dead yet?

35:52.442 --> 35:56.859
I don't know. I shot the shit
out of the tiles though.

36:08.250 --> 36:10.750
Okay, okay. I'll be right out.

36:13.005 --> 36:16.672
They ought to give
my grandmother a job here.

36:17.926 --> 36:21.260
If you're staying, it's 20 more dollars.

36:30.898 --> 36:32.608
Uh-

36:37.112 --> 36:41.033
Uh, the thing is, uh- is 16 good?

36:41.116 --> 36:43.619
No, 20 is good.

37:46.848 --> 37:48.433
Bitch.

39:49.137 --> 39:52.849
Let's get out of here.

40:03.902 --> 40:05.946
<i>Lee and I had crossed</i>
<i>that straight line</i>

40:06.029 --> 40:07.823
<i>that Dad called the law,</i>

40:07.906 --> 40:09.991
<i>and I could feel the butterflies</i>
<i>in my stomach</i>

40:10.075 --> 40:13.328
<i>as I tumbled deeper</i>
<i>into a life of crime.</i>

40:13.412 --> 40:16.415
<i>After all, murder was thicker</i>
<i>than marriage,</i>

40:16.498 --> 40:20.498
<i>and Lee and I were now bound</i>
<i>by the life we took.</i>

40:21.461 --> 40:24.589
<i>Being a wanted man</i>
<i>made Lee restless,</i>

40:24.673 --> 40:29.594
<i>and he swore he'd never sleep soundly
until we were well out of Florida.</i>

40:29.678 --> 40:32.431
<i>So he stole</i>
<i>his mother's record collection</i>

40:32.514 --> 40:35.684
<i>figuring even if we only got</i>
<i>a dollar a record,</i>

40:35.767 --> 40:37.936
<i>we would still have enough money</i>
<i>to fill the tank</i>

40:38.019 --> 40:42.186
<i>and make Miami a mere speck</i>
<i>in our rearview mirror.</i>

41:14.723 --> 41:17.392
It was just like
I told the officer last night.

41:17.476 --> 41:19.144
I heard some voices and some rustlin'.

41:19.227 --> 41:21.688
I got my light. I came out back.

41:21.771 --> 41:23.482
I saw her sitting right over there,

41:23.565 --> 41:26.026
pointing a gun right at me.

41:26.109 --> 41:28.820
It was as if she
was there waiting for me.

41:28.904 --> 41:34.238
Did you get a look at the person
she was with? No, sir, I didn't.

41:36.578 --> 41:38.246
I'm driving.

42:46.982 --> 42:48.984
He's waitin'.

42:49.067 --> 42:50.694
Couple minutes go by.

42:50.777 --> 42:53.071
So she finally walks up,
and the guy's all dressed.

42:53.154 --> 42:54.739
She goes, "Hey, where you goin'?"

42:54.823 --> 42:56.849
"I already shit in your purse."
I've heard it.

42:56.933 --> 42:59.100
Oh, shit on you. Hey, man.

43:02.414 --> 43:06.914
You got some really nice-
This is real nice stuff here.

43:09.170 --> 43:11.965
You know, but basically,
I only deal in jazz, you know, so, uh-

43:12.048 --> 43:14.467
You ought to hang on to that stuff.

43:14.551 --> 43:17.262
Hey, arrest that guy. He walked out
in the middle of my sentence.

43:17.345 --> 43:19.147
Yeah? Which joke were you tellin'?

43:19.230 --> 43:24.564
Aw, youth today, man. Nothing's sacred.
Startin' to realize that.

43:26.021 --> 43:28.106
Blue Note.

43:28.189 --> 43:29.774
Yeah, right here.

43:30.859 --> 43:32.027
Ryder.

43:35.113 --> 43:36.948
Okay, we're on our way.

43:37.032 --> 43:38.533
Come on.
Okay.

43:46.625 --> 43:48.501
What if I'd been at home?

43:48.585 --> 43:50.754
Has he ever
gotten physical with you?

43:50.837 --> 43:52.380
Or his mother?

43:52.464 --> 43:56.384
Oh, he's never taken a strike at me,
but the language-

43:56.468 --> 44:00.388
The language he uses is just awful.

44:00.472 --> 44:02.223
That doesn't count.

44:02.307 --> 44:04.392
Well, it should.

44:06.936 --> 44:09.731
You dust this?
No, it's clean.

44:09.814 --> 44:13.443
Anyway, to-
to make a long story short,

44:13.526 --> 44:15.654
by 6:00 we're all eatin'
this barbecued goat,

44:15.737 --> 44:18.156
drinkin' beer and so forth.

44:18.239 --> 44:21.993
Things are goin' along nicely,
and Clark, he's being really low-key,

44:22.077 --> 44:24.204
which is a nice change of pace
for Clark.

44:24.287 --> 44:26.998
You familiar with any
of his high school teachers?

44:27.082 --> 44:29.501
Specifically a Mr. Humphrey.

44:29.584 --> 44:30.835
Tall black man?

44:30.919 --> 44:35.548
High school? He's almost 30
years old, for Christ's sake.

44:35.632 --> 44:39.719
You know, you don't seem
too surprised by all of this.

44:39.803 --> 44:42.597
Isn't this strange behavior
for your son?

44:42.681 --> 44:46.393
Well, he took my heels.
That was a bit strange.

44:46.476 --> 44:48.895
Oh, he's all mixed up.

44:50.438 --> 44:53.650
So all night long as, uh,
people finish eating,

44:53.733 --> 44:57.946
they're stacking their plates
of leftovers out near the truck.

44:58.029 --> 45:01.449
The odd thing is, the dog never seems
to be the slightest bit interested.

45:01.533 --> 45:04.911
He just stays under the truck
ignoring the food.

45:04.994 --> 45:08.790
Now, it's not the nature of a dog
to ignore food like that.

45:08.873 --> 45:12.711
Well, before long, Garret realizes
the dog isn't under the truck.

45:12.794 --> 45:15.922
J.C., is this really
the short version of the story?

45:16.005 --> 45:17.882
You get what I'm saying to you?

45:17.966 --> 45:19.759
That was no goddamn goat
we barbecued.

45:19.843 --> 45:21.677
That was Garret's dog.

45:22.470 --> 45:25.470
Clark, he's a- He's a fuckin' sicko.

45:26.349 --> 45:29.561
Some people say
it's like a disease, you know?

45:29.644 --> 45:33.981
Once you start,
you can't stop till you're all filled up.

45:34.065 --> 45:36.443
Spider's pretty much filled up.

45:36.526 --> 45:39.779
He's got this... cobra that starts

45:39.863 --> 45:41.948
way up on his shoulder.

45:42.031 --> 45:45.948
Kind of drapes down
and covers his entire chest.

45:46.327 --> 45:48.994
Used to be a tattoo of his wife.

45:50.248 --> 45:52.500
But if you look real close you can see

45:52.584 --> 45:56.334
how the cobra's head
was once the wife's face.

45:57.630 --> 46:00.216
See, he used the original eyes.

46:00.300 --> 46:03.634
The wife's eyes
are now the cobra's eyes.

46:05.764 --> 46:09.848
Spider always said his wife
was half snake anyway.

46:48.973 --> 46:52.393
I told you already.
He'll be back in a little while.

46:52.477 --> 46:55.146
He'll come to your office
and pay you then, all right?

46:55.230 --> 46:57.524
Well, I hope so.

47:32.684 --> 47:34.686
<i>Lee hadn't slept well in two nights</i>

47:34.769 --> 47:37.105
<i>on account of</i>
<i>we were still in Dade County</i>

47:37.188 --> 47:41.276
<i>in the very neighborhood</i>
<i>where we had shot a man dead.</i>

47:41.359 --> 47:45.822
<i>Since my purse and photo ID had</i>
<i>been left at the scene of the crime,</i>

47:45.905 --> 47:48.199
<i>Lee said</i>
<i>I should hang back at the motel</i>

47:48.283 --> 47:50.785
<i>and remain out of sight.</i>

47:50.869 --> 47:53.121
<i>Anyways,</i>
<i>I didn't know much about holdups</i>

47:53.204 --> 47:58.204
<i>and Lee didn't want me</i>
<i>gettin' in the way of his crime spree.</i>

49:02.482 --> 49:04.275
Hey!

49:04.359 --> 49:07.987
You know you breakin' the law, man,
comin' in here with your shoes off?

49:08.071 --> 49:10.490
There's a dress code in Dade County.

49:10.573 --> 49:16.240
Go ahead and get what the hell
you want and get the hell out of here.

49:54.867 --> 49:56.619
11.60, sir.

50:06.713 --> 50:08.589
11.60, sir.

50:10.258 --> 50:14.595
What's the matter with you?
You understand English? 1 1.60.

50:14.679 --> 50:17.263
Don't move. Get back. Get back!

50:24.147 --> 50:26.899
- Sucker. - Hey, man, you gotta
pay. Come back here. Hey!

50:26.983 --> 50:31.150
You owe me money!
Bring my fuckin' money back here!

51:00.308 --> 51:03.436
We used to go to
River Ranch's campgrounds

51:03.519 --> 51:05.897
two weekends out of every month.

51:05.980 --> 51:10.151
Those two weekends
could get really crazy.

51:10.234 --> 51:12.734
My mom could get pretty crazy.

51:14.072 --> 51:17.075
You know, she could out-drink
just about anybody, man or woman,

51:17.158 --> 51:19.325
regardless of body weight.

51:20.620 --> 51:25.249
I remember this one time my dad
came crashing into the camper.

51:25.333 --> 51:27.710
My mom hated anybody
quitting a party,

51:27.794 --> 51:29.754
and I could hear her outside yellin',

51:29.837 --> 51:33.841
"Jimmy, this is the devil. I want
you to come out and play with me."

51:33.925 --> 51:36.344
And my dad yelled out,
"And this is God,

51:36.427 --> 51:40.348
and if you don't shut up,
I'm gonna strike you dead."

51:40.431 --> 51:43.518
Well, that left just Carl and my mom.

51:44.560 --> 51:46.687
Carl ran the campgrounds.

51:48.022 --> 51:50.942
Anyways, the party broke up
kind of early the next morning

51:51.025 --> 51:54.362
when my dad threw all our junk
in the camper.

51:54.445 --> 51:56.529
I was still up in my bed.

51:58.324 --> 52:03.162
Just then he just slammed the camper
door and hopped in his truck,

52:03.246 --> 52:06.374
and- and drove off.

52:06.457 --> 52:09.544
I rode the whole way home
in the back of the camper,

52:09.627 --> 52:12.794
not even knowing
my mom wasn't with us.

52:23.891 --> 52:25.810
The spent bullet is marked.

52:25.893 --> 52:29.480
McGwire's the one that found the flaw
in Jimmy's gun in the first place.

52:29.564 --> 52:31.023
He coined it "the crapper,"

52:31.107 --> 52:33.985
and he's certain that the bullet
fired at Humphrey

52:34.068 --> 52:37.818
is the same bullet
that came from Ryder's gun.

52:45.163 --> 52:47.456
The way I see things,

52:47.540 --> 52:49.417
you used to have two problems-

52:49.500 --> 52:52.503
a missing daughter
and a missing gun.

52:53.337 --> 52:55.381
The way it looks now,

52:55.464 --> 52:58.131
they're really the same problem.

53:31.876 --> 53:36.797
Do you think there's some girl
standing in a motel room far away

53:36.881 --> 53:40.381
lookin' at a picture
and thinking about me?

53:42.053 --> 53:43.554
I doubt it.

53:47.642 --> 53:49.894
She finds men to marry her.

53:51.812 --> 53:54.190
Recently she's been
in a bit of a slump,

53:54.273 --> 53:56.817
but she'll bounce back.

53:57.902 --> 54:00.652
My real father married her twice.

54:01.572 --> 54:03.908
Their second honeymoon,

54:03.991 --> 54:07.325
we all went to stay down
on Key Biscayne.

54:08.204 --> 54:11.499
They just started
goin' at it in the same old way,

54:11.582 --> 54:13.582
yellin' their heads off.

54:15.044 --> 54:20.007
So right out of the blue,
my dad just gets up off the couch,

54:20.091 --> 54:22.468
walks out the door,

54:22.551 --> 54:24.387
keeps on walkin'

54:25.346 --> 54:27.096
right into the ocean.

54:29.100 --> 54:31.184
Still had his clothes on.

54:32.478 --> 54:35.812
Probably still
had his drink in his hand.

54:37.441 --> 54:40.778
Anyway, the point is, about a half
a minute after they buried my dad,

54:40.861 --> 54:43.695
my mom made the fuckin' mortician.

54:44.865 --> 54:47.702
What a fuckin' creepy guy he was.

54:47.785 --> 54:49.704
Leopold.

54:49.787 --> 54:52.540
A fuckin' creepy mortician.

54:54.208 --> 54:56.958
Very creepy living with that guy.

55:31.329 --> 55:33.873
11:00. Twenty more dollars.

56:43.567 --> 56:45.945
Hey, roachy.

57:06.674 --> 57:10.010
<i>It's funny how a person could</i>
<i>leave everything she knew behind</i>

57:10.094 --> 57:13.594
<i>and still wind up</i>
<i>in such a familiar place.</i>

57:33.909 --> 57:37.371
<i>I stood near the water,</i>
<i>thinking about different things</i>

57:37.455 --> 57:39.415
<i>and sometimes catching</i>
<i>a glimpse of my life,</i>

57:39.498 --> 57:43.210
<i>as if I was thumbing</i>
<i>through an old photo album.</i>

57:43.294 --> 57:47.840
<i>I saw my dad being young</i>
<i>and playing jazz in our Florida room</i>

57:47.923 --> 57:52.052
<i>while my mom laid naked</i>
<i>on the cold terrazzo floor.</i>

57:52.136 --> 57:54.722
<i>I saw Bobby</i>
<i>in his black-and-white uniform,</i>

57:54.805 --> 57:57.183
<i>and I could almost smell</i>
<i>that restaurant stench</i>

57:57.266 --> 58:00.394
<i>that had become</i>
<i>so much a part of him.</i>

58:00.478 --> 58:04.231
<i>And I saw Lee in his blue car</i>
<i>nearly runnin' me down,</i>

58:04.315 --> 58:08.482
<i>looking so much like a guy</i>
<i>on his way to somewhere.</i>

58:46.190 --> 58:48.776
Come on, Jimmy,
let me take you home.

58:48.859 --> 58:51.111
Nah, this'll do fine.

58:51.195 --> 58:52.696
Everybody's leaving.

58:52.780 --> 58:56.280
Anyway, you don't wanna
start drinkin' now.

58:56.450 --> 58:59.620
What's she doin' with this guy?

58:59.703 --> 59:03.832
I think the thing to do is go ahead
and put an APB out on these kids.

59:03.916 --> 59:05.918
She's no kid.

01:01:06.955 --> 01:01:09.166
New York City?
Yeah.

01:02:00.801 --> 01:02:03.968
I'd like a refund, please.
Cash refund.

01:02:14.565 --> 01:02:17.732
They're a little old.
I never used 'em.

01:02:56.565 --> 01:02:59.234
<i>Oh, shit!</i>

01:03:12.539 --> 01:03:14.625
Come on, come on, come on.
What- What is up?

01:03:14.708 --> 01:03:19.792
We're gettin' out of here. You
look like you just saw a ghost.

01:03:20.547 --> 01:03:22.174
Aren't we gettin' on the bus?

01:03:22.257 --> 01:03:24.134
That place was filled
with fuckin' deadbeats.

01:03:24.218 --> 01:03:26.553
I don't see anything.
You weren't in there.

01:03:26.637 --> 01:03:29.848
What about New York?
We can drive to New York.

01:03:29.932 --> 01:03:33.060
Damn it! I hate buses.
I can't even get on a fuckin' bus.

01:03:33.143 --> 01:03:36.560
Well, what were we
doin' at a bus station?

01:04:26.196 --> 01:04:27.698
Shit.

01:04:32.119 --> 01:04:35.455
You got any money? Me? No,
I don't have any money.

01:04:35.539 --> 01:04:37.624
I don't have the fuckin' toll.

01:04:37.708 --> 01:04:39.710
We need a quarter.

01:04:49.219 --> 01:04:51.386
What the fuck we gonna do?

01:04:53.140 --> 01:04:55.225
Cozy, come on.
Run it.

01:04:55.309 --> 01:04:56.977
We can't run it.
Go!

01:04:58.353 --> 01:05:00.981
Shit.

01:05:07.070 --> 01:05:11.570
You have to pull over there
to the side for me, please.

01:05:50.948 --> 01:05:54.615
May I see your license
and registration? Yes.

01:06:00.791 --> 01:06:05.041
Just your license and registration,
not your wallet.

01:06:11.468 --> 01:06:13.720
Lee Ray Harold, North Miami?

01:06:13.804 --> 01:06:15.555
That's you?
Yep.

01:06:24.481 --> 01:06:26.358
Lee, this is your car?

01:06:26.441 --> 01:06:28.610
Yeah.
Mm-hmm.

01:06:28.694 --> 01:06:30.988
All right, I'm going
to ask both of you to sit right here

01:06:31.071 --> 01:06:32.988
till I come back, okay?

01:06:39.413 --> 01:06:41.832
Lee, we're through. Just be still.
Everything's okay.

01:06:41.915 --> 01:06:44.084
What is okay?
Where's the gun?

01:06:44.167 --> 01:06:45.919
What are you gonna do with it?
Nothing.

01:06:46.003 --> 01:06:49.089
Lee, he's calling on his radio.
He's gonna find out.

01:06:49.172 --> 01:06:51.174
- Cozy, where the fuck is the gun?
- You can't shoot a cop.

01:06:51.258 --> 01:06:53.260
I'm not gonna shoot the
fuckin'- Let me drive.

01:06:53.343 --> 01:06:55.178
Jesus, Cozy, will you cool it?
Let me drive!

01:06:55.262 --> 01:06:59.512
We didn't kill anybody.
He wasn't even fuckin' hurt.

01:07:03.687 --> 01:07:06.604
Lee, do you have money with you?
Um-

01:07:07.649 --> 01:07:10.027
You do know this is a toll road?
Yeah.

01:07:10.110 --> 01:07:15.610
Florida Highway Patrol doesn't tread
lightly on toll-gate crashers.

01:07:15.991 --> 01:07:18.160
You still at this
North Miami address?

01:07:18.243 --> 01:07:20.537
Yeah.
Okay.

01:07:22.039 --> 01:07:23.540
Tell you what I'm gonna ask you to do.

01:07:23.623 --> 01:07:26.043
I want you to turn your car
completely around

01:07:26.126 --> 01:07:30.005
and head on back home
to North Miami.

01:07:30.088 --> 01:07:32.716
And the next time you think
you wanna take a ride on a toll road,

01:07:32.799 --> 01:07:35.469
you make sure you have money
in your pocket

01:07:35.552 --> 01:07:37.637
and a cool head on your shoulders.

01:07:37.721 --> 01:07:39.222
You hear me?
Yeah.

01:07:39.306 --> 01:07:41.266
Okay.

01:07:41.349 --> 01:07:43.018
You take care now.

01:08:24.850 --> 01:08:27.354
<i>Suddenly, I wasn't sure of anything.</i>

01:08:27.437 --> 01:08:30.148
<i>I wasn't on the lam after all.</i>

01:08:30.232 --> 01:08:32.609
<i>I wasn't layin' low or ducking cops,</i>

01:08:32.692 --> 01:08:36.029
<i>and if I was, no one cared.</i>

01:08:36.113 --> 01:08:38.448
<i>We hadn't killed anybody.</i>

01:08:38.532 --> 01:08:43.828
<i>I couldn't even be sure we had really killed
the palmetto bug back in the motel room.</i>

01:08:43.912 --> 01:08:48.125
<i>So if we weren't killers,</i>
<i>we weren't anything.</i>

01:08:49.126 --> 01:08:51.211
Cozy, I'm sorry.

01:08:53.796 --> 01:08:58.214
I was gonna tell you
as soon as we got out of Florida.

01:10:02.032 --> 01:10:07.537
You know my friend Doug and his girlfriend
Julia, they have this apartment.

01:10:07.621 --> 01:10:13.455
It's not too big, but the rent's
pretty cheap. We could stay with them.

01:10:14.211 --> 01:10:18.295
I could get a job.
Maybe get two jobs for a while.

01:10:19.966 --> 01:10:22.050
Get some money comin' in.

01:10:27.557 --> 01:10:30.891
Couple months,
we could get an apartment.

01:10:31.228 --> 01:10:33.563
Maybe in the same complex.

